<br>
Philosophy:  Guilds are designed to support the desires and needs of individuals.  When one item or quest is too difficult to handle solo, then groups are formed.  But we have come together because we each saw a need to be a part of a family in a game that demands people to group together to achieve a goal.  EQ has a LOT of carrots and sticks within its codes.  &quot;Raids&quot; therefore, are needed to be coordinated so that individuals (ultimately the guild) get the rewards of playing the game.<br>
<br>
Idea #1<br>
1) PLEASE /tell me or post under &quot;guild request&quot; your desires for the guild to raid.<br>
2) I WILL be making a calander for the events and posting it on the message board (or getting the web designer to do that for me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
3) For total guild support please allow time for your request to be done - I will post raids on the Brell board so that we can get more people involved.  Layha has requested a 2 week minimum and I agree with this, but please do not expect your request to be fulfilled within that time frame - BUT I PROMISE IT WILL BE DONE<br>
<br>
Now then - the guild already has some priorities and I think everyone would agree with one of them ... Cleric Epics.  Some guildies are already tryin to drum up support and that is awesome.  Cleric epics are our highest priority right now.  <br>
<br>
Idea #2:<br>
A monthly (or biweekly) event to handle epic requests.  If everyone knows that on the first week of every month is a raid for an epic piece then you can adjust your game and RL calendar to support your guild.<br>
<br>
Im sure everyone wants their epic... one piece at a time.  In time we can become a powerful guild simply because our members have the combat ability to do it - in number AND items.<br>
<br>
Sorry it was long... please let me know what you think.<br>
